Mary Thicknesse-Touchet, 22nd Baroness Audley (13 August 1858 – 27 May 1942).
Mary Thicknesse-Touchet was eldest daughter of George Edward Thicknesse-Touchet, 21st Baron Audley (1817–1872) and Emily Mitchell. She never married.
She obtained her title by writ on the death of her younger sister, Anne, on 17 May 1937. It had been in abeyance since the death of her father in 1872.
Mary Thicknesse-Touchet died on 27 May 1942. On her death her title passed by writ to her second cousin, Thomas Touchet-Jesson, 23rd Baron Audley (1913 – 1963).

response: He inherited the title of 23rd Baron Audley on 27 May 1942 by writ, succeeding his second cousin Mary Thicknesse-Touchet, 22nd Baroness Audley on her death. As he died childless on 3 July 1963, the title passed to his sister Rosina (1911–1973).

Thicknesse-Touchet died on 18 April 1872 in Bad Homburg, Germany and was buried in Frankfurt. On his death his title went into abeyance until restored by writ to his eldest daughter, Mary Thicknesse-Touchet, 22nd Baroness Audley (1858–1942) on the death in 1937 of her younger sister.
